6 "SECTION 2. That Chapter 12, Title 39, Idaho Code, be, and the same is
7 hereby amended by the addition thereto of a NEW SECTION, to be known and des-
8 ignated as Section 39-1211C, and to read as follows:
9 39-1211C. FOSTER PARENT TRAINING. (1) Each caregiver, unless exempted,
10 shall complete training on knowledge and skills relating to the reasonable
11 and prudent parent standard as set forth in chapter 16, title 16, Idaho Code.
12 (2) The department shall make training available on an ongoing basis on
13 the following topics: rights, roles, and responsibilities of foster par-
14 ents; laws and regulations; the impact of childhood trauma; managing child
15 behaviors; first aid and medication administration; gun safety in foster
16 homes; and the importance of maintaining meaningful connections between the
17 child and parents, including regular visitation."
18 ; and renumber succeeding sections accordingly.
